Line and clustered column chart - Death weeks 17

In this step we are going to build a line and clustered column chart in our report that shows death week over week since the start of the pandemic.

That being said, the goal is to create a report  that shows mortality rate for the last 12 weeks from the maximum date of selection. Now that our calculated columns that display dynamic x-axis and our measure are created lets create the death week report.

Steps for this report

1. Drag and drop line and clustered column chart from visualizations.

2. Drag and drop

  • Week duration column from calendar table to shared axis in fields box
  • Last 12 weeks from calendar table to shared axis in fields box
  • Mortality Rate from measure table to column values in fields box
  • Deaths WOW% from measure table to line values in fields box
  • Total deaths from measure table to tooltips in fields box
  • Total cases from measure table to tooltips in fields box

3. Legend - on

  • Color - White, 20% darker
  • Font family - Arial
  • Text size - 10pt
  • Style - Line and markers

4. X-axis - on

  • Color - White, 20% darker
  • Text size - 9pt
  • Font family - Arial
  • Title - off

5. Y-axis - on

  • Color - White, 20% darker
  • Text size - 9pt
  • Font family - Arial
  • Display units - None
  • Title - off
  • Stroke width - 1
  • Line style - Dotted
  • Show secondary - on
  • Aline zeros - on
  • Y-Axis line :

                           - Color - #f79a7e, theme color 8, 40% lighter

                                      -  Text size - 9pt

                           - Font family - Arial

                           - Value decimal place - auto 

                           - Title - off

6. Data colors 

  • Death WOW% color -  #f47853, Theme color 8, 20% lighter
  • Default color - #f9bba9, Theme color 8, 60% lighter

7. Data label - on

  • Color - White, 10% darker
  • Display units - None
  • Text size - 9pt
  • Font family - Arial
  • Customize series - on

                                                - Select - Mortality Rate                                                              - Select - Death WOW%

                                               - Color -  #f9bba9, Theme color 8, 60% lighter               - Color - #f79a7e, theme color 8, 40% lighter

                                               - Display units - None                                                       

                                                - Text size - 9pt

                                                - Font family - Arial

                                                - Show back ground - on

                                                - Back ground color - White, 60% darker  

                                                - Transparency - 33    

 8. Shapes 

  • Shade area - on                                                                                        

 9. Title - on 

  • Add a title text and use same format through out the dashboard ( Refer step 4)

10. Boarder - on

  • Color - Black, 40% lighter

11. In the filter pane under Last 12 weeks filter, select - Last 12 weeks.
